PROBLEM STATMENTS --> from interview yesterday --> 

GA has a growth mindset and is always improving! To that end, they've hired you as a 
UX Designer to improve on the current student experience, either academically or socially.--> Business Objective 

Questions

How do you feel about the way the available resources are organized? Slack/ google drive 
Which resource do you like to use the most?     Why? 
Which resource do you like to use the least?    Why? 
do you feel that the way in which things are ordered is an accurate representatin of the GA brand? if so why?
Tell me about a time, if any, that you felt frustrated with the resources available.     
Can you tell more about that?    
With your current knowledge, how do you feel about the UX of the academic resources at GA?     
What, if anything, would you change?

